==English==
===Noun===
[[Category:English nouns]]
# The act of burying someone alive.
#:'''quotations''':
#:*"Thus, to characterize the Victorian worry about premature burial as a product of 'morbid romanticism,' or of the 'sheer mythopoeic force' of '''vivisepulture''', is to ignore the deep confusion over human physiology that persisted into the twentieth century. &mdash; ''Journal of British Studies'', April 2003

=== Pronunciations ===
vive-uh-sep-uhl-chur

=== Etymology ===
French prefix vivi-, English sepulture

=== Information ===
Vivisepulture was the winning word of Wendy Guey in the 1996 Scripps National Spelling Bee.